      skos:note "Call-notes format with heavy embedded verbatim block-quotes from two speakers. David's quoted speech is expansive and probing (~28 words avg per sentence); Scarlet's editorial prose is shorter and declarative (~18 words avg). Active voice dominant in editorial sections. Jargon density low-moderate — product terms (perspective, introspect, conviction stack, white space) used without definition, implying internal audience. Antithesis-heavy structure (developer vs. management, siloing-as-bug vs. feature, demo-value vs. own-data-required). Consistent with Scarlet session-memo idiolect." .

